HEADWORD: Poetize
<hw>Po"et*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Poetized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Poetizing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>po⟦eacute⟧tiser</ets>.]</ety> <def>To write as a poet; to compose
verse; to idealize.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I versify the truth, not <qex>poetize</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Donne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

